# Error Handling

## Custom Errors

Define domain-specific errors extending `Error`; use for structured handling and HTTP mapping.

```typescript
// lib/errors.ts
export class ValidationError extends Error {
  constructor(message: string, public readonly field?: string) {
    super(message);
    this.name = 'ValidationError';
  }
}
export class AuthError extends Error {}
export class NotFoundError extends Error {}
```

## Server-Side: Log and Rethrow

- Modules and lib: `throw new Error(...)` or custom errors.
- In catch: **log first**, then **re-throw**; never empty catch.
- Only the **boundary** (route, Server Action) converts to HTTP status.

```typescript
// ❌ BAD
try {
  await doSomething();
} catch (e) {}

// ✅ GOOD
try {
  await doSomething();
} catch (e) {
  logger.error('[MODULE] Operation failed', { error: e });
  throw e;
}
```

## HTTP Mapping (Route Handlers / Server Actions)

| Error type | Status |
|------------|--------|
| ValidationError | 400 |
| AuthError | 401/403 |
| NotFoundError | 404 |
| Other | 500 |

```typescript
// app/api/patients/route.ts
catch (e) {
  if (e instanceof ValidationError) return Response.json({ error: e.message }, { status: 400 });
  if (e instanceof AuthError) return Response.json({ error: 'Unauthorized' }, { status: 401 });
  if (e instanceof NotFoundError) return Response.json({ error: 'Not found' }, { status: 404 });
  logger.error('[API] Unexpected error', { error: e });
  return Response.json({ error: 'Internal error' }, { status: 500 });
}
```

## React: Error Boundary

Use Error Boundary to catch render errors and show a fallback UI.

```tsx
// components/error-boundary.tsx
'use client';
export function ErrorBoundary({ children, fallback }: { children: React.ReactNode; fallback: React.ReactNode }) {
  return (
    <ErrorBoundaryInner fallback={fallback}>
      {children}
    </ErrorBoundaryInner>
  );
}
// Use React's use() or a small library; wrap key sections.
```

## Next.js Conventions

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `error.tsx` | Catches errors in route segment; must be Client Component |
| `not-found.tsx` | Rendered when `notFound()` is called |
| `global-error.tsx` | Catches root layout errors; replaces root layout |
| `loading.tsx` | Loading UI ( Suspense ) |

```tsx
// app/dashboard/error.tsx
'use client';
export default function DashboardError({ error, reset }: { error: Error; reset: () => void }) {
  return (
    <div>
      <p>Algo deu errado.</p>
      <button onClick={reset}>Tentar novamente</button>
    </div>
  );
}
```

```tsx
// app/not-found.tsx
export default function NotFound() {
  return <h1>Página não encontrada</h1>;
}
```

## Client-Side Forms and Mutations

- Validate with Zod + react-hook-form; show field errors in PT-BR.
- For mutations: catch in `onError` or `try/catch`; show toast or inline message.
- Do not let unhandled promise rejections reach the user; always show a message.
